est": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/pulls/11947", "html_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/11947", "diff_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/11947.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/11947.patch"}, "body_html": "<p>The MPI async work class returned a temporary as reference, which is<br>\ninvalid (hat tip to <a class=\"user-mention\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/hovercards?user_id=655866\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/colesbury\">@colesbury</a> for noticing it). This change fixes that and<br>\nuses a std::exception_ptr to hold on to the exception if applicable, and<br>\nthen returns the reference by throwing it and returning it, like the<br>\nexisting code path.</p>", "body_text": "The MPI async work class returned a temporary as reference, which is\ninvalid (hat tip to @colesbury for noticing it). This change fixes that and\nuses a std::exception_ptr to hold on to the exception if applicable, and\nthen returns the reference by throwing it and returning it, like the\nexisting code path.", "body": "The MPI async work class returned a temporary as reference, which is\r\ninvalid (hat tip to @colesbury for noticing it). This change fixes that and\r\nuses a std::exception_ptr to hold on to the exception if applicable, and\r\nthen returns the reference by throwing it and returning it, like the\r\nexisting code path.\r\n\r\n"}